wikipedia_page.main: James Grinham (christened 20 December 1798 at Godalming, Surrey; details of death unknown) was an English amateur cricketer who played first-class cricket from 1822 to 1835.  He was mainly associated with Sussex and made 13 known appearances in first-class matches including 1 for the Gentlemen.
